4together with result\nil ant actions\u2014can make the\ndifference In llf.lng the|\neconomy to higher and higher,\nlevels.\nIt to at this point that the\nwisdom, the venturesomeness,\nthe resourcefulness of our busi\nness leadership are put to the\ntest.\nWe have about \u201ccaught our\nbreath.\u201d\nThere 1s nothing wrong with\nour oxygen supply\nNow, what do we do to get\nclimbing again?\nStresses Private Action\nThe emphasis of this confer\nence to on private action, and\nrightly so. But we all know\nthat the Job of recovery to a\njoint effort In which business\nleaders, labor leaders, farm\nI\nleaders, professional leaders,\nconsumers, together with Gov\nernment. must all play a part\nI could not in good conscience\ncome here tonight and call on\nyou as businessmen to do your i\nfull part unless I felt confident!:\nthat the Government was fully i\nalert to its own responsibility I\nGovernment\u2014while It can\nnot guarantee prosperity\u2014has\na continuing responsibility In h\ntimes like these to use its\npowers to help counteract re- i\ncession. It has a duty to al- i\nlevlate human hardship and\nprotect our human resources,\nIto help promote an upturn In\nproduction and employment,\nand to help build a solid foun\ndation for long-term growth.\nAll this It should seek to do in\naway that strengthens the vi\ntality of our private enterprise\nsystem, and that Includes safe-\nYoungblood Paint Hdw.\n\u202241 Cadar St., Takoma Park N.W. j\nSA. 3-3481\nVIRGINIA\nMiller's Hardware\n800 King St., Alexandria, Va.\nKing 9-1157\nl\nBradlee Hdw. and Supply\n3682 King St., Al\u00abx.. Va., OV. 3-4300\nJames Hardware\n5801 Im Hwy.. Arl., Va., KE. 3-6173\nJB. 7-7200\nWilliamsburg Hardware\n2914 N. Sycamore St., Arl., Va. JE. 4-0779\nS. Kann Sons Co.\nArlington, Vq., Dl. 7-7200\nMARYLAND\nColor Center\n406 E. Montgomery Avenue\nRockville, Md., PO. 2-3662\nGray Bldg. Supply Co.\n7700 Marlboro Pike\nPorestville, Md., IE 5-5050\nPark Paint Hdwe.\nlex ington Pork, AMI. VOfcgiteer\nguarding th\u00ab Integrity of our\ncurrency.\nCarrying out this responsi\nbility. your Government has\nacted over a period of many\nmonths In many ways to coun\nter the recession and foster\nrecovery. Let me cite the main\nItems In this record of action\nAction in 5 Fields\nFirst, the Independent Fed\neral Reserve System has In\ncreased the availability of credit\nand helped reduce Its cost to\nborrowers.\nSecond, a series of actions\nstarting last August has been\ntaken to promote private hous\ning construction and to step\nup activity In such fields as\nurban renewal and college\nhousing.\nThird, measures have been\ntaken toward accelerating ap\nproved construction In many\ncategories, such aa poet office\nmodernisation, water resource\nprojects, hospitals and high\nways. The accent has been on\nthe speeding up of going or\nauthorised work on needed fa\ncilities. I am determined not\nto get bogged down In a slow\nstarting, emergency public\nworks program, which would\nprovide a minimum of Jobs now\nand a maximum of budgetary\nheadaches In the years ahead.\nOne truth we should always\nhold before our eyes: Reckless\nexpenditure In the name of\neconomic stimulation to both\nwrong and self-defeating.\nFourth, steps have been tak\nen to accelerate markedly pro\ncurement for needed defense\nand civilian requirements.\nFifth, recommendations have\nbeen made to Congress to deal\nwith special problems. An ex\nample to my proposal of March\n25 to provide temporary unem\nployment Insurance benefits to\nindividuals who have exhausted\ntheir regular benefits. This pro\nposal goes directly to the heart\nof the problem of relieving hu\nman hardship arising from the\nrecession. There can be argu\nments about the details, but\nthere to no arguing about the\npersonal anxiety and hardship\nthat this proposal will alleviate.\nI .1 I\n2-IN-1 VALUE!\nCRIB PLUS\nMATTR ESS\nfW v it I fl Mmjl\nMill r i 1\nPftUL I- I\nmki 11 nJ| U p\nSPECIALLY PRICED! EDISON CRIB\nCOMPLETE WITH ITS OWN MATTRESS\nAIL Northern hardwood in non-toxic white,\nwox birch or maple finish with gay Both For Only\nnursery decals. Has 4-position spring od-\njustment. double drop sides and plastic jfl fIA(EJk\nteething roils. Mattress is a solid block of /l\ncurled rubberized lotex hoir covered in\no heavy laminated fabric goy nursery\nprint and wet-proof.\nTHE HECHT CO. RIGHT PRICE INFANTS\u2019 FI/HJVITI RE\nMfr. List 24.95 Step-fold Play Yard, wax birch 14.86\nMfr. List 11.95 Taylor Tot Stroller-Walker 8.88\nDeeco Play-Safe Play\u2019Yard, strong nylon sides 24.99\nMfr. List 9.95 Bassinette, folds for storing 6.88\nPortacrib with 3\" Mattress is a play yard, too $22\nMfr. List 22.95 Strolee Stroller with canopy 18.44\nINFANTS' FURNITURE\u20142nd Floor, Washington: ith Floor, Silver Spring;\n3rd Floor, PARKington\n1 \"I 1111 \u25a0\u25a0\u25a0_.\nWe need Its prompt enactment\nby the Congress.\nTax Decision Dae\nThere to another area of pol\nicy that has aroused Intense\nInterest, both In and out of\nGovernment. That to taxation.\nEveryone in this country to.\n1 know, concerned about taxa\ntion. We would like to achieve\nimprovements In the tax struc\nture. We would like to assure\nmaximum equity In the tax\nburden. Ws would like to.\nachieve further simplification.\nWe would like a tax structure\nwhich least Interferes with\nsound economic growth.\nThe timing of such changes!\nalways poses problems. During\nperiods of high business activ\nity and high employment there\nIs concern with Inflationary ef\nfects. In a time like the present,\nwith Its rising Government ex\npenditures, we are particularly\nsensitive to tax burdens, but\nthere is likewise great concern\nwith the future Impact of In\ncreasing current deficits.\nAfter consultation with con\ngressional leaders, certainly de\ncisions will shortly be taken in\nthe field of taxation. They will\nbe made In the light of the\nlatest Information regarding\nthe economic situation and with\na full evaluation of the prob\nable short and long range con\nsequences This matter of\ntaxation to so Important to the\nAmerican people that by no\nmeans should it be the subject\nof political competition.\nWhile we are talking of\nGovernment activity, we can\nnot forget defense reorganiza\ntion. mutual aid and world\ntrade. Through our security\nestablishment, we help produce\nthe confidence essential to\nprosperty at home. Through\nour mutual aid program we\nhelp other free-world nations\ndevelop their strength In order\nto maintain their defense estab\nlishments against Communist\nthreats, and In order to bring\nthe economic Improvement\nthat spells hope for their peo\nple. And through expanding\nworld trade we Increase Jobs\nat home and economic strength\nhere and abroad. In these\nthree vital areas ws need de\ncisive congressional action.\nPleased by Aettoa\nNow I want to turn to the\nfield of private business notion\nI have been gratified by the\nunderlying purpose and ac\ncomplishments of this confer\nence. Business loaders have\nbeen reporting precisely what\nthey and their Industries are\ndoing In creating new products\nand designs, reducing costs,\nmodernising plants and facili\nties, and merchandising more\neffectively. All this will create\nnew and better Job opportu\nnities. These reports show that\nAmerican businessmen are en\ngaged more and more In the\nbest kind of creative competi\ntion-investing their resources,\ntheir ambitions, their imagi\nnations and themselves to build\nstronger positions for their\ncompanies. Thus they will help\nbuild a stronger America and\na stronger free world.\nThey do this because they\nare deeply convinced of this\nplain truth about American life:\nAchievement and progress\ncannot be created for our peo\nple: they can only be created\nby our people.\nAmericans would have It no\nother way. Our future to In\nour own hands. Our prospects\nare limited only by our vision\nand by our exertions.\nPredicts Records\nOur economy has always\nmoved ahead to set new records\nafter every period of pause or\nrecession In our history.\nIt will do so again.\nOne salient fact should be\nclear. We can never pep-talk\nour way to prosperity No one\nhere to proposing that we try.\nWe are simply suggesting that\nbusinesses do what to clearly In\ntheir own interest. We are sug\ngesting, further, that It be done\nin the time-honored American\nway of self-reliance and self\nstarting initiative. Our economy\nhas grown strong because our\npeople have made Jobs for each\nother and have not relied on\nBoth For Only\nthe Government to try to do ft\nfor them.\nWhat to our economy anyway?\nEmphatically our economy to\nnot the Federal Reserve Bys\ntem. or the Treasury, or the\nCongress, or the White House.\nThis Nation of 43 million fam\nilies, 174 million people\u2014what\nwe all think and what we do\u2014\nthat to our economy.\nOur economy to the result of\nmillions of decisions we all\nmake every day about produc\ning. earning, saving, investing\nand spending. Both our Indi\nvidual prosperity, and our Na\ntion's prosperity, rest directly\non the decisions all of us are\nmaking now.\nGaldee for Decision*\nThis conference has been\nconcerned with guides for such\ndecisions by business. Let us\nlook at a few.\nThe first to this: The best\nSAMPSON'S OAK CLUB Club Special\nB|\u00a7|gi 7-year-old 100 proof 7-year-old Bottled in Exfro dry for the perfect rs|||l|\u00a7\nBottled in Bond Straight Bond Straight Kentucky martini or your favorite I\n|Pp||ii\u00a7j Bourbon. Bourbon. 86 proof. long drinks. 86 proof. |ig||||||\n2* 8 Fifth 2*68 Fifth J. 45 Fifth\nCHAMPAGNE for June weddings\ns B ROCHER PERE ET FILS, PIERRE LUCIEN \u2014New IMPORTED ITALIAN Cham- M\nv H Brut 1952. A fine ,m- York State's finest. Nat- jflgii\nported French Cham- urally fermented in the ASTI SPUMANTE\npogne. bottle. nebioio spumante\nMB (Sparkling lurgundy)\n2'\u00ae* Fifth 0-58 Fifth\n4* 1A\nCose of 12, $33 79 Cost of 12, $29 \u00bb7 As' FiWl\nill CHECK THESE BEER SPECIALS gif